The paper discusses program synthesis and repair, which are topics that fall under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of syntax-driven search and term grammars suggests that the paper may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL). The use of probabilistic models and input-output examples suggests that the paper may be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the implementation of the algorithm in a framework for verification suggests that the paper may also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
